 The SPR performs the functions of voter registration and review of the voter register based on the following 3 sources of authority:
Articles 113 and 119 of the Federal Constitution;
Elections Act 1958;
 andThe Elections (Registration of Voters) Regulations 2002.

The categories of absentee voters consist of
Regularly serving military personnel;
Spouses of regular military personnel;
Policemen other than members of the Reserve Volunteer Police Force;
Spouse to General Operations Force police;
Civil servants serving abroad
Spouses of civil servants serving abroad
Students abroad on a full-time basis
Spouses of full-time overseas students
